quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  32,12,"And if you could see the criminals protruding their heads in the Reckoning with their Lord, (saying), \"Our Lord, we have beheld and heard; so return us, that we may do righteousness. (Now) surely we have certitude"
  32,13,"And if We had so decided, indeed We could have brought every self its guidance; but (now) the Saying from Me has come true: \"Indeed I will definitely fill Hell with jinn (creatures) and mankind all together"
  32,14,So taste for that you forgot the meeting of this your Day! Surely We have forgotten you. And taste the torment of eternity for whatever you were doing
  32,15,"Surely only they believe in Our signs who, when they are reminded of them, collapse constantly prostrating and extol with the praise of their Lord, and they do not wax proud.* A prostration is to be performed here"
  32,16,"Their sides often shun (their) recumbencies (i.e., beds, places for reclining) to invoke their Lord in fear and in longing (from Him); and they expend of what We have provided them"
  32,17,So no self knows what is (kept) concealed for them in comfort of the eyes as a recompense for whatever they were doing
  32,18,"So, is he who has been a believer like him who has been immoral? They are not equal"
  32,19,"As for the ones who have believed and done deeds of righteousness, then for them are the Gardens of Abode as quarters for whatever they were doing"
  32,20,"And as for the ones who have been immoral, then their abode will be the Fire. Whenever they would (like) to go out of it, they will be brought back into it, and it will be said to them, \"Taste the torment of the Fire, which you used to cry lies to"